article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 70, Army 61
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Reed Baker scored 26 points to lead Florida Gulf Coast to a 71-60 win against Army on Tuesday night. FGCU held a 25-point lead against Army, then survived a furious second-half comeback to seal the win. Baker hit four 3-pointers and Delvin Franklin scored all of his 14 points in the first half on 4-of-7 shooting from behind the arc. FGCU (5-8) led 40-23 at halftime and opened a 53-30 lead early in the second half on three consecutive 3-pointers, including two from Baker, who matched his career high with four 3s. Army (3-9) trailed 59-34 midway through the second half but used 25-5 run to cut the deficit to five points with just less than 2 minutes remaining. Kenny Brewer scored eight of his team-high 16 points in that run for Army.
